{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01544Jq3xwaZpfgWAB2KjjMb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpackage metrics\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"net/http\"\n5\t\n6\t\t\"github.com/cornjacket/platform/internal/metrics/handlers\"\n7\t\t\"github.com/cornjacket/platform/internal/metrics/store\"\n8\t)\n9\t\n10\t// New wires the event store and HTTP handlers together and returns the\n11\t// resulting http.Handler. Routes: POST /events, GET /events.\n12\tfunc New() http.Handler {\n13\t\ts := store.New()\n14\t\th := handlers.New(s)\n15\t\n16\t\tmux := http.NewServeMux()\n17\t\tmux.HandleFunc(\"/events\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n18\t\t\tswitch r.Method {\n19\t\t\tcase http.MethodPost:\n20\t\t\t\th.PostEvents(w, r)\n21\t\t\tcase http.MethodGet:\n22\t\t\t\th.GetEvents(w, r)\n23\t\t\tdefault:\n24\t\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"method not allowed\", http.StatusMethodNotAllowed)\n25\t\t\t}\n26\t\t})\n27\t\n28\t\treturn mux\n29\t}\n30\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ac686bb-e9d7-4d59-95bc-ffb853866775","uuid":"d2ae2b92-fd9f-419e-828d-50beb2a78f35","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:34:48.513Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/metrics.go","content":"package metrics\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cornjacket/platform/internal/metrics/handlers\"\n\t\"github.com/cornjacket/platform/internal/metrics/store\"\n)\n\n// New wires the event store and HTTP handlers together and returns the\n// resulting http.Handler. Routes: POST /events, GET /events.\nfunc New() http.Handler {\n\ts := store.New()\n\th := handlers.New(s)\n\n\tmux := http.NewServeMux()\n\tmux.HandleFunc(\"/events\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\t\tswitch r.Method {\n\t\tcase http.MethodPost:\n\t\t\th.PostEvents(w, r)\n\t\tcase http.MethodGet:\n\t\t\th.GetEvents(w, r)\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"method not allowed\", http.StatusMethodNotAllowed)\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\n\treturn mux\n}\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":30}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dy7VERdiS6PinESNJzw4KQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context. The pre-existing README.md is comprehensive and covers Purpose/Tags, file index, overview, API contract, and data model. I need to:\n\n1. Check if it's stale — it looks complete and accurate based on the handoff summaries and metrics.go source\n2. Write `metrics.go.md` — documents the metrics.go wiring file\n3. Write `data-flow.md` — shows data flow between handlers and store\n4. Update README.md to add links to data-flow.md and metrics.go.md if they're not there\n\nThe pre-existing README.md is missing:\n\n\n- A link to `data-flow.md` (which I'll write)\n- A link to `metrics.go.md` (which I'll write)\n- The component table for sub-components (handlers/ and store/)\n\nSo I need to update the README.md to include a component table with links to handlers/README.md and store/README.md, plus links to the synthesis docs. Now I'll start writing those three files.\n\nFor `metrics.go.md`, I'm documenting how New() wires everything together—it creates the store, injects it into the handlers, registers the /events route with method dispatch, and returns the mux. For `data-flow.md`, I'm mapping out both the startup sequence (New() → store.New() → handlers.New() → mux.HandleFunc) and the request-time flow (HTTP request → mux → method dispatch → store operations). Then I'll update the README to include the component table and links to these synthesis docs while keeping the existing content intact.\n\nNow I need to add links to both data-flow.md and metrics.go.md in the README, and update the Tags section to include 'overview'.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1136,"cache_read_input_tokens":21296,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1136},"output